A Lagos-based Industrialist, Dr Olusegun Aderemi, has appealed to the Federal Government and the Nigeria Labour Congress (NLC) to take steps to avert a national strike over planned fuel subsidy removal. Aderemi, who is the Atayero of Aramoko Ekiti, also urged Ekiti people to conduct themselves peacefully during the June 18 governorship election. He said an industrial action of that magnitude at this time will bring about the total collapse of the economy. Read Also: Investors’ suit to recover N11.79b resumes Feb 12   Law firm, NGO partner on gender violence eradication     Investors’ suit to recover N11.79b resumes Feb 12     Prayers held for Bello’s presidential ambition,…   The Chief Executive Officer of Autofit and Energy spoke in Aramoko Ekiti, where he distributed business guide books to over 300 young entrepreneurs in the community. - Advertisement - According to him, the initiative is to raise as many entrepreneurs as possible in the community in particular and Ekiti at large. “I want to teach the people how to fish rather than giving them fishes always. My projection is for these beneficiaries to mentor other entrepreneurs,” Aderemi said. Aderemi noted that the labour was doing what the constitution empowers it to do by fighting for the masses, urging the government to have listening ears.